{"id":"7192","name":"Convert Base64 to Hexstring [JS1]","tagline":"A JavaScript one-liner to convert a base64 string to an hexadecimal string","icon":"ios12 c255 g59853","latest":"22260","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>A single line of JavaScript to recode data from base64 (6 bits/character) to hexadecimal (4 bits/character). This allows a basic level of manipulation of binary data. It should be used together with my \"Convert Hexstring to Base64 [JS1]\" shortcut.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No error checking</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://editor.scpl.dev/?scpl=%40Icon%20font%0A%40Color%20darkgray%0AComment%20%22A%20JavaScript%20one-liner%20to%20convert%20a%20base64%20string%20to%20an%20hexstring%20%20%E2%80%94%20%40atnbueno%20%282020-10-25%29%5Cn%5Cn-%20No%20error%20checking%22%0AText%20%22iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAACwAAAAsAgMAAABj6rKSAAAACVBMVEWVk47T0Mn59e1hOL86AAAAF0lEQVR42mNkQABGLQfCbFGHUfXDWD0AmZsRKZoxaCwAAAAASUVORK5CYII%3D%22%20-%3E%20mv%3AText%0AURL%20%22data%3Atext%2Fhtml%2C%3Cscript%3Edocument.write%28%5B...atob%28%27%5C%28mv%3AText%29%27%29%5D.map%28c%3D%3Ec.charCodeAt%280%29.toString%2816%29.padStart%282%2C0%29%29.join%28%27%27%29%29%3C%2Fscript%3E%22%0AGetFileofType%20%22com.apple.webarchive%22%20-%3E%20mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%0AText%20%22Input%3A%5Cn%5C%28mv%3AText%29%5Cn%5CnOutput%3A%5Cn%5C%28mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%7Bas%3A%20text%7D%29%22%0AQuickLook\">ScPL source</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Spread_syntax\">Spread syntax (...)</a> and <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Glossary/Base64\">Base64</a> documentation at MDN</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Don't download the shortcut</h4>\n<p>If you just want the code, there's no need to download the shortcut. Copy this and paste it in a \"URL\" action:</p>\n<pre><code>data:text/html,&lt;script&gt;document.write([...atob('REPLACEWITHBASE64VARIABLE')].map(c=&gt;c.charCodeAt(0).toString(16).padStart(2,0)).join(''))&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Replace the <code>REPLACEWITHBASE64VARIABLE</code> fragment with the variable contaning the base64 string, add a \"Get File of Type\" with type <code>com.apple.webarchive</code> below, and its output will be the hexadecimal string. Show it with a \"Quick Look\" action to see it (a \"Show Results\" is not adequate because of the text centering and hyphenation).</p>\n<p>I use \"Get File of Type\" instead of \"Get Contents of Webpage\" to avoid that the user is misleading told that the shortcut uses Safari.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Oct. 25, 2020, 4:11 p.m.</strong></p>"}